gitCommit.subject: Refactor editor toolbar to a floating UI and update selection handling
gitCommit.body:
Refactor editor toolbar to a floating UI and update selection handling

- Add `toolbarPosition` signal in `Editor.tsx` to compute and store the cursor selection coordinates; hide the toolbar when the selection is empty or in markdown mode.
- Replace the static toolbar with a new floating toolbar (`floatingToolbar` class) that is positioned via inline `top`/`left` styles and styled with borders, shadow, and transition effects.
- Remove mode‑toggle buttons from `EditorToolbar`; introduce a separate mode‑toggle container in `Editor.tsx` with its own styling (`modeToggleContainer`) and active button styling.
- Update CSS: rename `.editorToolbar` to `.floatingToolbar`, add positioning, visual enhancements, and adjust mobile media queries accordingly; add `.modeToggleContainer` styling.
- Adjust `EditorToolbar` props: drop `editorMode` and mode‑switch callbacks, add optional `position` prop, render the toolbar only when a valid position is provided.
- Revise E2E tests (`e2e/editor-toolbar.spec.ts`) to use double‑clicks or text selection (`selectText`) on list items and task items, ensuring the selection is active so the floating toolbar appears.
- New `e2e/floating-toolbar.spec.ts` validates that the floating toolbar is hidden on load, appears when text is selected, and hides again on blur, while the mode‑toggle remains visible.
- `EditorToolbar.tsx` now renders the toolbar only when a valid `position` is provided and includes `data-testid="floating-toolbar"` to make it selectable in tests.
- Introduce `toolbarModeToggle` and related button styles in `Editor.module.css`.
- In `Editor.tsx` implement `toggleMode`, add a `Ctrl+Shift+M` key handler, and pass `editorMode` + `onToggleMode` to `EditorToolbar`.
- Extend `EditorToolbar` props to receive `editorMode` and `onToggleMode`; render a mode‑toggle button group inside the floating toolbar using the new CSS classes.
- Update the toolbar UI to include the mode toggle beside formatting controls, replacing the previous separate mode‑toggle container.
- Remove the now‑unused `.modeToggleContainer` and `.modeButton` styles.
- Introduce `.modeIndicator`/`.modeIndicatorActive` for a minimal toggle displayed at the editor’s bottom‑right.
- Update `Editor.tsx` to drop the old mode‑toggle container, render the new `modeIndicator` UI, and continue passing `editorMode` + `onToggleMode` to `EditorToolbar`.
- Restore the mode‑toggle button group inside `EditorToolbar` (styled via `.toolbarModeToggle`) with proper `data-testid`s.
- Introduce `toolbarModeToggle` and related button styles in `Editor.module.css`.
- In `Editor.tsx` implement `toggleMode`, add a `Ctrl+Shift+M` key handler, and pass `editorMode` + `onToggleMode` to `EditorToolbar`.
- Extend `EditorToolbar` props to receive `editorMode` and `onToggleMode`; render a mode‑toggle button group inside the floating toolbar using the new CSS classes.
- Update the toolbar UI to include the mode toggle beside formatting controls, replacing the previous separate mode‑toggle container.
- Remove the Visual/Markdown toggle buttons from `EditorToolbar` and drop the `editorMode`/`onToggleMode` props.
- Add a new `.modeIndicator` element in `Editor.tsx` with two buttons (`editor-mode-visual`, `editor-mode-markdown`) that stay visible regardless of selection.
- Adjust CSS (`Editor.module.css`) to style the new indicator and remove the old toolbar‑toggle styles.
- Update `Editor.tsx` to render the indicator and handle mode switching via `switchToWysiwyg` / `switchToMarkdown`.
- Simplify `EditorToolbar` to only render formatting buttons based on the provided `position`.

Pretty big deal!
